"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-paris-olympians-sebastian-coe-university-of-portsmouth-new-zealand-b2564287.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Leading athletes and climate scientists have warned that extreme heat will make it \\\"impossible\\\" to hold the Olympics during the summer months amid fears of dangerous conditions at this year'sParisGames.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A group ofOlympianscollaborated with climate scientists and heat physiologists from theUniversity of Portsmouthto assess the threat warming temperatures could pose for athletes.\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a report, published on Tuesday, they warned that intense heat at the Paris Olympics in July-August 2024 could lead to competitors collapsing and in worst-case scenarios dying during the Games.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think in a lot of places, in the US and around the world, summertime competitions unless they are held in the middle of the night are going to become essentially impossible  One of the report's recommendations includes changing the traditional schedules of competitions so that they take place in cooler months or cooler times of day.\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 1262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 961, \"end\": 963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9953136591551225, \"rank\": 0.004707130185599655, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking to reporters ahead of its release, Kaitlyn Trudeau, senior research associate at Climate Central, said: \\\"Without concerted efforts to reduce carbon emissions there is no doubt that the Earth's temperatures are on a trajectory that will make it nearly impossible, if not completely impossible, to host summer Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1308, \"end\": 1315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\", \"score\": 0.9957241429440393, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaitlyn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\"}, {\"begin\": 1316, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Trudeau\", \"score\": 0.9999998754942758, \"rank\": 1.2450587927295965e-07, \"text\": \"Trudeau\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Trudeau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Trudeau\"}, {\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Climate_Central\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Climate Central\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Climate_Central\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Climate_Central\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Trudeau added that extreme heat combined with humidity means the body struggles to cool down, which can lead to heat-stress on bodies, dizziness, exhaustion and heat stroke.\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1596, \"end\": 1603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Trudeau\", \"score\": 0.9999998754942758, \"rank\": 1.2450587927295965e-07, \"text\": \"Trudeau\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Trudeau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Trudeau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Samuel Mattis, a discus thrower on the American Olympic team, said hot conditions disrupted the Olympic track and field trials in 2021, which eventually had to take place in the evening even though it was still around 30C.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999955678602412, \"rank\": 4.432089085244111e-06, \"text\": \"American Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think in a lot of places, in the US and around the world, summertime competitions unless they are held in the middle of the night are going to become essentially impossible,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2031, \"end\": 2033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9953136591551225, \"rank\": 0.004707130185599655, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamie Farndale, a Team GB rugby sevens player, said that extreme heat \\\"takes a lot away from you\\\" as you play.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2183, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamie_Farndale\", \"score\": 0.9999966823898384, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jamie Farndale\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamie_Farndale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamie_Farndale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I found myself in these conditions where you are literally trying to get through the next phase of play, your hands are sweaty, you (can only) concentrate on catching the ball so I think it makes a worse game.\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also dangerous.\\\"\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The British player said he wanted the sports sector to sound an \\\"alarm bell\\\" to prevent warming as well as look at adaptation methods such as moving the schedules.\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2533, \"end\": 2540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999814030016361, \"rank\": 0.0001843053297931648, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We need to fight for every tenth of a degree that we possibly can  \\\"We need to fight for every tenth of a degree that we possibly can,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The climate researchers looked at how temperatures have changed since the Olympics were last hosted in Paris and France a century ago in 1924, with analysis suggesting an average 3.1C warming for those weeks in July and August.\", \"from\": 2840, \"to\": 3067, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2943, \"end\": 2948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.188888165885933e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2953, \"end\": 2959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9994876360233109, \"rank\": 0.00032551028980255976, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They found a heightened risk of extreme heat at the Paris Games this year, citing the deadly heatwave in France in 2003 - which killed more than 14,000 people - and subsequent years of record-breaking temperatures, exceeding 42C.\", \"from\": 3069, \"to\": 3298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9994876360233109, \"rank\": 0.00032551028980255976, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It comes after the Tokyo Games in 2020 became known as the \\\"hottest in history\\\", with temperatures exceeding 34C and humidity reaching nearly 70%.\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking about those Games, Marcus Daniell, aNew Zealandtennis player and Olympic bronze medallist, said: \\\"I felt like the heat was bordering on true risk - the type of risk that could potentially be fatal.\\\"\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3476, \"end\": 3482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\", \"score\": 0.9998605304560525, \"rank\": 0.00013948899841785932, \"text\": \"Marcus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcus_Aurelius\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, Pragnya Mohan, the highest-ranking triathlete in Indian history, said she can no longer train in her home country because of the heat.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3668, \"end\": 3681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pragnya_Mohan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999131433, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pragnya Mohan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pragnya_Mohan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pragnya_Mohan\"}, {\"begin\": 3717, \"end\": 3731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_India\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Indian history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She added that sponsors want \\\"more visibility\\\" so events tend to be held in the afternoons for maximum public turnout, meaning she has competed in \\\"extremely dangerous\\\" conditions with 40C-plus temperatures and humidity was 80%-plus.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 4037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The report produced by the British Association for Sustainable Sport and FrontRunners outlined five recommendations to better support and protect athletes from extreme heat.\", \"from\": 4039, \"to\": 4212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4112, \"end\": 4124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FrontRunners\", \"score\": 0.669467902590356, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FrontRunners\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FrontRunners\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FrontRunners\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With global temperatures continuing to rise, climate change should increasingly be viewed as an existential threat to sport  Alongside smarter scheduling to avoid heat extremes, these were urging sporting authorities to introduce better rehydration and cooling plans for athletes, empowering athletes to speak out on climate change, boosting collaboration between sporting bodies and athletes on climate awareness campaigns, and reassessing fossil fuel sponsorship in sport.\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4688, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"LordSebastian Coe, president of World Athletics and four-time Olympic medallist, said: \\\"For athletes, from smaller performance-impacting issues like sleep disruption and last-minute changes to event timings, to exacerbated health impacts and heat-related stress and injury, the consequences can be varied and wide-ranging.\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 5012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4722, \"end\": 4737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999974493221, \"rank\": 2.5507591697974915e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With global temperatures continuing to rise, climate change should increasingly be viewed as an existential threat to sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other athletes involved in the report were Hannah Mills, British Olympic sailing champion, Imogen Grant, British Olympic rower, Eliza McCartney, a New Zealand bronze Olympic medallist in pole vault, Kelsey-Lee Barber, Australian Olympic bronze medallist in javelin, Rhydian Cowley, an Australian Olympic racewalker, Ajla Del Ponte, a Swiss Olympic springer, Elena Vallortigara, Italian high jump Olympian, Morten Thorsby, a Norwegian footballer, Jenny Casson, a Canadian Olympic rower, and Katie Rood, a New Zealand football player.\", \"from\": 5142, \"to\": 5674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5185, \"end\": 5197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mills\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3657380376559308e-22, \"text\": \"Hannah Mills\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mills\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mills\"}, {\"begin\": 5199, \"end\": 5206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999814030016361, \"rank\": 0.0001843053297931648, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 5233, \"end\": 5245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imogen Grant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\"}, {\"begin\": 5247, \"end\": 5254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999814030016361, \"rank\": 0.0001843053297931648, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 5270, \"end\": 5285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliza_McCartney\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eliza McCartney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliza_McCartney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliza_McCartney\"}, {\"begin\": 5289, \"end\": 5300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9281830166315076, \"rank\": 0.028783214387340033, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5341, \"end\": 5358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey-Lee_Barber\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelsey-Lee Barber\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey-Lee_Barber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey-Lee_Barber\"}, {\"begin\": 5360, \"end\": 5370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.7004408373283609, \"rank\": 0.4276664393030382, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 5408, \"end\": 5415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhydian_Roberts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.684486025269873e-17, \"text\": \"Rhydian\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhydian_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhydian_Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 5416, \"end\": 5422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plant_Oxford\", \"score\": 0.998120889508275, \"rank\": 0.0018826481955433983, \"text\": \"Cowley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plant_Oxford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plant_Oxford\"}, {\"begin\": 5427, \"end\": 5437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.7004408373283609, \"rank\": 0.4276664393030382, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 5458, \"end\": 5472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ajla_Del_Ponte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ajla Del Ponte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ajla_Del_Ponte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ajla_Del_Ponte\"}, {\"begin\": 5476, \"end\": 5481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999786563921085, \"rank\": 2.1344046385913256e-05, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 5500, \"end\": 5518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_Vallortigara\", \"score\": 0.9999983996830524, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elena Vallortigara\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_Vallortigara\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elena_Vallortigara\"}, {\"begin\": 5520, \"end\": 5527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.6742417967274104, \"rank\": 0.46188700334336763, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 5538, \"end\": 5546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9996075729468401, \"rank\": 0.00039258111242547206, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 5548, \"end\": 5562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morten_Thorsby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Morten Thorsby\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morten_Thorsby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morten_Thorsby\"}, {\"begin\": 5566, \"end\": 5575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.9999991630651358, \"rank\": 8.101856697328567e-07, \"text\": \"Norwegian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 5604, \"end\": 5612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.5559604564787134, \"rank\": 0.7986890710286287, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 5632, \"end\": 5642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Rood\", \"score\": 0.9999980240651407, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Rood\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Rood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Rood\"}, {\"begin\": 5646, \"end\": 5657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9281830166315076, \"rank\": 0.028783214387